# React + TypeScript

## React

- Functional components and hooks only
- Colocate styles in sibling `.css` files; no CSS-in-JS unless requested
- Use `type="button"` on non-submit buttons
- Default export for page-level components; named exports for utilities and hooks

## TypeScript

- Strict mode — do not weaken types or use `any`
- `interface` for component props; `type` for unions and utilities
- Non-null assertions (`!`) only when guaranteed (e.g. `getElementById('root')`)

## Example

```tsx
interface ButtonProps {
  label: string
  onClick: () => void
}

export function Button({ label, onClick }: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button type="button" onClick={onClick}>
      {label}
    </button>
  )
}
```
